1
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:03,040
Uncle Ree, what are you doing?

2
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:03,960
Hey!

3
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:06,400
Rajit!

4
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,520
<i>Don't ever do this again.</i>

5
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:09,520
I was worried about you, okay?

6
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:14,320
I'm not surprised
to see you here every day.

7
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,720
What exactly do you want?

8
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:17,840
All I ask for is your forgiveness, Rajit.

9
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,600
According to my detective,

10
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,880
Kajorn already has a wife,

11
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,440
but they aren't legally married.

12
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,200
Is anyone home?

13
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:34,520
You…

14
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:46,400
Hey, you.

15
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,680
You're Suda, right?

16
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:18,960
And you are?

17
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:22,080
I'm Thatri, Rajit's uncle.

18
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:25,560
I went to your house
and found you unconscious,

19
00:03:25,640 --> 00:03:27,800
so I rushed you here to see the doctor.

20
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:30,480
Are you feeling any better now?

21
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:33,120
I'm feeling a bit better now.

22
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:38,240
There's no need to rush.
Just lie down for a bit.

23
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:48,560
Thank you so much for taking
the trouble to bring me here.

24
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,080
It's no trouble at all.

25
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,440
I actually came to see you
because I need your help.

26
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,480
What is it?

27
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,400
It's about Kajorn.

28
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:21,279
Thank you so much for bringing me home.

29
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,520
Don't mention it.

30
00:04:29,960 --> 00:04:31,960
Looking at the state of this house,

31
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,440
you probably wouldn't believe

32
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,240
that a girl from a wealthy family,

33
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:40,720
who could afford to study in Penang
like me, would end up living here.

34
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,640
The lowest point of my life

35
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:48,280
all started with that man named Kajorn.

36
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:50,400
If you don't want to end up dead,

37
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,000
get out of my house right now.

38
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,800
Father, stop. Please don't hurt him.

39
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:56,720
This pimp is just using you for money.

40
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,200
Can't you see that? Huh?

41
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:01,680
That's not true.
Kajorn loves me. I'm certain of it.

42
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:04,080
I truly love Suda, sir.

43
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,200
Suda, please.

44
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,920
Open your eyes, my child.
Listen to your father.

45
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,520
He's only trying to protect you.

46
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,600
I don't believe you.

47
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,400
If you really loved me,

48
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:16,080
you'd let me marry him.

49
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:18,440
The only reason you're refusing

50
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:20,520
is because you don't love me.

51
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,600
You're just protecting
your precious fortune.

52
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,720
Please, sir.

53
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:28,200
I really do love her.

54
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:31,280
Liar! I don't believe you!

55
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:33,240
Let us get married, please.

56
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:37,880
Please, Father. I'm begging you.

57
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:40,120
Please.

58
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:49,840
If you're going to shoot Kajorn,

59
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,840
then you'll have to shoot me too.

60
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:55,760
Fine. You love him that much?

61
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:58,520
Then both of you, get the hell
out of my house right now!

62
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,520
And mark my words,

63
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,280
once you walk out that door,
you're no longer welcome here.

64
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,240
Now go!

65
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:09,480
Get out of my house! Leave!

66
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:13,040
Leave!

67
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,200
You're back, Kajorn?

68
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,600
Huh?

69
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:52,880
Can't you see past your own filth?

70
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,440
I'm standing right here, aren't I?

71
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,160
Of course, I'm back.

72
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:02,840
You must be exhausted. Are you hungry?
I can fix you something to eat.

73
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:04,440
I'm not eating.

74
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:08,680
Just looking at your face
makes me want to puke.

75
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:11,000
Understand?

76
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,760
- Ouch.
- Hey.

77
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:14,400
Now tell me.

78
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:18,000
When the hell are your parents
going to accept me, huh?

79
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,080
Huh?

80
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:23,480
But even if they don't,
we still have our love.

81
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:25,440
To hell with love, you idiot.

82
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,160
I threw away my fortune

83
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:29,480
just to live in this miserable dump?

84
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:39,800
We actually had some savings at first.

85
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:42,160
But we lost everything

86
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:44,000
because of your gambling, didn't we?

87
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:45,360
Huh?

88
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:50,040
You've got quite a mouth on you today.

89
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:53,120
You're asking for it, aren't you?

90
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,320
Fine.

91
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:06,560
Damn it.

92
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:07,880
Always talking back.

93
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:12,160
These stairs are so steep.

94
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,960
- Where are you going?
- Stay away from me.

95
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:02,320
I'm going back to Rajit.

96
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,960
You found out she inherited
that fortune, didn't you?

97
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:06,400
That's why you're leaving me.

98
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,560
Damn right.

99
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:09,840
Why would I stay in this dump with you?

100
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:13,920
You're broke, you're sick,
and you look like a corpse each day.

101
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:16,840
No, Kajorn!

102
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:19,720
Please don't leave me.
I truly have no one else left.

103
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,400
Like I give a damn!

104
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,880
Kajorn, please.

105
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:29,400
I'm begging you. Please, stay with me.

106
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,600
Let go.

107
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:37,360
No. Please don't leave me.

108
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:38,800
Let go!

109
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,080
I said let go!

110
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,880
Damn it!

111
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:11,880
I keep playing back my friends' warnings
in my head every single day

112
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:17,760
that I would eventually regret my choices.

113
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:21,800
And now, I truly have no one left.

114
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:26,640
How are you getting by these days?

115
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:31,040
After Kajorn left,

116
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,520
I lost my baby.

117
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:36,080
My body is failing,

118
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,760
and now I have tuberculosis.

119
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:45,480
If my employers find out
how sick I really am,

120
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:49,120
I don't know
how much longer they'll keep me.

121
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:57,720
You're a total stranger.

122
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:00,560
Why are you pleading
on behalf of my ungrateful daughter?

123
00:11:00,640 --> 00:11:02,560
I may be a stranger,

124
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:05,320
but I truly could not bear
to see her in such a pitiful state.

125
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:08,800
Is her condition really that bad?

126
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:10,120
Dear.

127
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:16,880
Sir,

128
00:11:18,760 --> 00:11:20,920
you might call her ungrateful,

129
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,720
but you still call her your daughter.

130
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:25,640
That word alone shows that deep down,

131
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:28,040
your love for her hasn't changed a bit.

132
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,960
Don't let your ego

133
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:38,080
come between you and your daughter.

134
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:42,040
Suda is gravely ill,

135
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:44,280
and we don't know
how much time she has left.

136
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:48,640
If you wait until it's too late,

137
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:52,880
all the love in the world
won't mean a thing.

138
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:16,480
PHUKET

139
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:19,560
Where on earth
did your owner disappear to, Don Jose?

140
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:41,080
Where have you been?

141
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,080
Were you waiting for me?

142
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,440
Who's waiting?

143
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:48,400
Hey, Don Jose,
were you waiting for your owner?

144
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,720
I take such good care of you,

145
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:53,440
even if he stayed away for years,

146
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:55,240
you wouldn't miss him at all, right?

147
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,080
Good to know.

148
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,200
So…

149
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:06,680
Where exactly did you go?

150
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:12,080
If you were waiting, just admit it.

151
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,760
It's not that hard.

152
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,200
I already told you, I wasn't waiting.

153
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:23,960
I just wanted to know
where have you been, that's all.

154
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:49,960
Everyone. I've told Nid
and Jiam to wait out front.

155
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:52,320
They'll lead you all
to the government shelter.

156
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,280
Aren't you two coming with us?

157
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:56,680
This sounds far worse than the last one.

158
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:58,280
Don't worry. We'll be right there.

159
00:13:58,360 --> 00:14:00,440
What about Aunt Fuang and Aunt Paetai?

160
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,480
I have no idea. I haven't seen them.

161
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,200
In that case, everyone go ahead.

162
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:05,320
I'm going to find them.

163
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:16,880
Aunt Fuang. Aunt Paetai.

164
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:18,680
Wait, Rajit.

165
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:20,840
Go now. I'll go after Rajit.

166
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,600
Let's go.

167
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:29,760
Aunt Fuang.

168
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:32,400
Aunt Fuang. Are you there?

169
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,800
Aunt Paetai.

170
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,760
Aunt Paetai.

171
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,000
Any sign of them?

172
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:43,720
I couldn't find anyone.

173
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:54,200
The bombing is getting too intense.
We'll never make it in time.

174
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:57,760
Wait. Before Grandpa passed away,

175
00:14:57,840 --> 00:15:01,080
he told me he'd built
a private family shelter

176
00:15:01,160 --> 00:15:02,800
in the backyard.

177
00:15:02,880 --> 00:15:05,960
He said to go there
in case of an emergency.

178
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:08,160
- Let's go.
- Okay, hurry.

179
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:15,440
Watch your step.

180
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,560
This way.

181
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:05,400
We should be safe now.
There's nothing left to fear.

182
00:16:18,560 --> 00:16:21,000
Hey. Whoa.

183
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:27,280
Grandpa stored
so much food in here, Uncle Ree.

184
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,800
We're all set for food.

185
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,960
Are you even worried?
You're always thinking with your stomach.

186
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:36,760
Well, I'm out of energy.

187
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,680
An army marches on its stomach.

188
00:16:38,760 --> 00:16:39,920
You know the saying, right?

189
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,360
Is that a stomach or a bottomless pit?

190
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,960
It's impossible to fill it up.

191
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:48,400
Hey.

192
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,760
This really takes me back.

193
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:08,880
Why? Are raisins your favorite?

194
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:12,440
Not really. It's just…

195
00:17:14,319 --> 00:17:16,920
When I was a kid, we were so poor.

196
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:21,079
I could never even touch treats like this.

197
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:25,920
When the neighbors had parties,

198
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,200
I'd just stand by the fence

199
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:31,200
and watch them eat.

200
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:35,240
I finally got to try them
when I came to live with Grandpa Som.

201
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:50,400
Why are you looking at me like that?

202
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:53,040
Do you feel sorry for me?

203
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:59,440
I'm fine, Uncle Ree.

204
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:01,560
That was a long time ago.

205
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:04,200
I keep it as a memory,

206
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:07,160
but now I live for the present

207
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:10,000
and dream of the future.

208
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:16,240
Dreaming of the future, huh?
Mind telling me what those dreams are?

209
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:20,640
That's a secret.

210
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:33,160
Here, I'll share some with you.

211
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:35,560
Thanks.

212
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:41,240
Just kidding. Here you go.

213
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,000
Is it good?

214
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:52,040
Delicious. Eat up. You need it to grow.

215
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:11,480
Rajit!

216
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,280
Hey!

217
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:15,640
That's herbal liquor.

218
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,160
You nearly drank the whole thing.

219
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:26,880
Hey, Don Jose.

220
00:19:27,840 --> 00:19:31,400
Your owner is so cruel.

221
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:34,280
He abandoned me.

222
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:39,480
Right, boy? He just left me.

223
00:19:40,400 --> 00:19:41,840
I knew it. You're drunk.

224
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:48,760
You're the guilty one,
and yet you're blaming me?

225
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:52,600
Watch it, or I'll have Don Jose bite you.

226
00:19:54,760 --> 00:19:57,760
Oh, look at that. A feisty drunk, I see.

227
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:04,240
Of course, it's because
I'm not good enough.

228
00:20:04,320 --> 00:20:06,480
That's why you left me, Uncle Ree.

229
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:11,080
I didn't leave you.
I had some business to take care of.

230
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:13,320
And I'm back now, aren't I?

231
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:15,600
I don't believe you.

232
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:18,360
Where did you go?

233
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:21,320
Tell me the truth, Uncle Ree.

234
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,320
I went to Bangkok.

235
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:29,280
Why didn't you say anything?

236
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:34,880
You have no idea what I had to go through

237
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:37,760
while you were gone.

238
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:39,960
Alright, tell me then.

239
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:42,040
What happened while I was gone?

240
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,440
While you were gone,

241
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:48,080
It was so suffocating.

242
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:52,880
I had to deal with Kajorn and Vijarn.

243
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:57,320
And then, when I went out
with Primprao and Nareewan,

244
00:20:57,400 --> 00:21:01,800
I was taken away
by someone I didn't even know.

245
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:06,000
On top of that, I had to work
with Aunt Paetai,

246
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:08,360
who nagged and bit at me every single day.

247
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:13,560
You don't get it, but when you left,

248
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:19,600
you took all my peace of mind with you.

249
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:37,320
I only went to Bangkok

250
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,360
because of you, you know.

251
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,480
If it's for me,

252
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:46,680
then don't go at all.

253
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:48,600
Because

254
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:53,000
I don't want to be
in this house without you.

255
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:59,720
I promise I'll never
leave you behind again.

256
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:01,720
What did you say, Uncle Ree?

257
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,200
I promise

258
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,000
I'll never leave you behind again.

259
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,600
Can you keep that promise?

260
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:25,120
Of course.

261
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:29,360
For you, I can do that.

262
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:46,520
Promise me.

263
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:53,560
Come on, promise.

264
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:00,400
I promise.

265
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:05,680
You promised, okay?

266
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:28,200
Rajit?

267
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:02,880
Rajit!

268
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:21,800
Don Jose, are you waking Mommy up?

269
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:40,760
What's that smell? It's disgusting.

270
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:48,920
You're finally awake?

271
00:24:56,760 --> 00:24:59,440
Uncle Ree, why do you smell so bad?

272
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:04,600
Don Jose, stay back. Come here, boy.

273
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:08,040
Your owner smells like
he's been rolling around in vomit.

274
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:14,320
Would a head-flick be ungentlemanly?

275
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:19,720
I'm going to puke. So smelly.

276
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:28,440
What's this, Auntie Jiam?

277
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:29,960
It's ginseng chicken soup.

278
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:33,400
Since you mentioned having a headache
from that herbal liquor,

279
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:35,880
I prepared this to help clear your head.

280
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:39,600
Just eat it already.

281
00:25:40,240 --> 00:25:42,760
Ginseng is hard enough to find as it is.

282
00:25:43,480 --> 00:25:46,040
Even in the middle of a war,
I can't believe you'd still

283
00:25:46,120 --> 00:25:48,080
go to such lengths for her.

284
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:51,680
This was kept by the master
specifically for his granddaughter.

285
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:54,360
That's why it wasn't offered
to anyone else.

286
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:08,000
Can I skip this?

287
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,400
I really can't stand the smell.

288
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:12,280
Not used to high-quality stuff, are you?

289
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:15,800
Typical of someone from your background.

290
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:18,600
Try to force it down, dear.

291
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:21,280
It works wonders for a hangover.

292
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:26,000
Just eat it. Maybe you'll stop
puking all over people.

293
00:26:26,080 --> 00:26:29,360
You eat it then,
if you like the smell so much.

294
00:26:29,440 --> 00:26:31,480
And why wouldn't I? It's just soup.

295
00:26:38,440 --> 00:26:39,520
This is incredible.

296
00:26:39,600 --> 00:26:41,960
It's simmered to perfection.
The broth is so sweet.

297
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:45,040
Thank you. I'll go get
a fresh one for you.

298
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:46,880
No need for that, Auntie Jiam.

299
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:49,960
If Uncle Ree can eat it, so can I.

300
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:04,600
Good heavens. How scandalous.

301
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:07,760
Oh my…

302
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:14,840
It's an old Chinese tradition, dear.

303
00:27:14,920 --> 00:27:18,080
But don't worry. People don't really
stick to it much these days.

304
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:25,120
What was that all about?
It's just chicken soup.

305
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:26,640
Why the dramatic reactions?

306
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:30,400
This specific jar,
it's called a Kam Cheng.

307
00:27:30,480 --> 00:27:32,040
In Hokkien Chinese,

308
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:33,920
it means a jar with a lid.

309
00:27:35,200 --> 00:27:37,240
Okay. And?

310
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:38,720
What's so strange about that?

311
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:39,840
Well,

312
00:27:41,040 --> 00:27:42,600
the word "Kam Cheng"

313
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:46,480
is a homophone for the word
meaning deep affection.

314
00:27:48,360 --> 00:27:50,400
Well, tradition dictates
that a bride and groom

315
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:52,640
share soup from the same jar

316
00:27:52,720 --> 00:27:54,640
to symbolize their lifelong bond.

317
00:27:55,760 --> 00:27:57,840
An unmarried man and woman

318
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:59,600
simply don't share the same jar.

319
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,600
I'll go get that new jar now.

320
00:28:19,800 --> 00:28:21,600
How's the hangover?

321
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:23,000
Still got that headache?

322
00:28:23,080 --> 00:28:24,360
It's gone.

323
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:27,280
I had no idea I was such a lightweight.

324
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:29,840
I only had a little bit.

325
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:31,320
You chugged half the jar in seconds.

326
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:32,920
I wouldn't call that a little bit.

327
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:39,360
Uncle Ree, besides puking on you,

328
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:42,720
did I do anything else embarrassing?

329
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:46,640
If it's for me,

330
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,440
then don't go at all.

331
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:55,200
Because I don't want to be
in this house without you.

332
00:28:57,000 --> 00:29:00,200
I promise I'll never
leave you behind again.

333
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:05,280
Can you keep that promise?

334
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:06,320
Of course.

335
00:29:07,960 --> 00:29:10,440
For you, I can do that.

336
00:29:23,080 --> 00:29:24,160
Nope.

337
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:28,120
You just threw up on me
and passed out. That's it.

338
00:29:30,080 --> 00:29:32,000
Your voice went a bit high there.

339
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:35,120
Did you want something to happen?
I'm telling the truth.

340
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:38,080
No, of course not.

341
00:29:41,120 --> 00:29:42,560
Mr. Thatri.

342
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:44,680
Mr. Thatri.

343
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:48,440
There's big trouble, sir.

344
00:29:57,680 --> 00:30:00,960
Last night's bombing
sank several cargo ships.

345
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:05,240
Goods are nearly impossible to find now.

346
00:30:06,080 --> 00:30:09,560
We're facing a severe emergency
across Phuket.

347
00:30:16,360 --> 00:30:18,560
- Primprao. Nareewan.
- Rajit.

348
00:30:25,360 --> 00:30:27,320
Are you guys okay?

349
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:29,560
My house is safe,

350
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:32,720
but my father said
the rice shipment was hit by a torpedo.

351
00:30:32,800 --> 00:30:34,320
Everything is lost.

352
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:42,440
The government issued ration cards.
Everything is strictly limited.

353
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:44,680
My family is so large,

354
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:46,720
I don't know if this will be enough.

355
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,960
It's going to be okay.

356
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:19,080
Mr. Thatri. Miss Rajit.

357
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:21,720
I've secured the ration cards
for everyone.

358
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:26,880
- Here you go, sir.
- Thank you.

359
00:31:28,840 --> 00:31:32,400
This should keep us going for a bit,

360
00:31:32,480 --> 00:31:35,160
but it won't last more than a month.

361
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:39,560
Let's hope we get fresh supplies
before mid-month.

362
00:31:39,640 --> 00:31:41,720
Otherwise, there will be riots.

363
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:55,320
- You thief!
- Stop!

364
00:31:55,400 --> 00:31:56,520
Stop that!

365
00:31:57,120 --> 00:31:58,200
Stop that right now!

366
00:31:58,280 --> 00:32:01,280
- I said stop.
- That's enough.

367
00:32:01,360 --> 00:32:02,760
Break it up.

368
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,240
You're a thief!

369
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:05,880
Break it up.

370
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:07,400
- You thief.
- Stop it!

371
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:08,520
Stop.

372
00:32:08,600 --> 00:32:09,840
I said stop!

373
00:32:15,680 --> 00:32:16,720
That's enough.

374
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:21,000
Yong, are you okay?

375
00:32:22,200 --> 00:32:25,800
What is going on here?
Why are you all fighting like this?

376
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:28,280
Yong stole my rice.

377
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:31,120
We already split the portions,
but this thief still wanted more.

378
00:32:31,840 --> 00:32:34,960
My kid was starving.
Would it kill you to spare for a child?

379
00:32:35,040 --> 00:32:37,560
That's your kid, not mine.
Why should I do that?

380
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,720
- Hey, stop!
- Stop.

381
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:41,040
I said stop!

382
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:50,520
This is my ration card. You can have it.

383
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:54,360
- Don't steal again. It's for the kid.
- But sir…

384
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:56,960
Now, take it.

385
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:01,520
Thank you, sir.

386
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:04,360
Mr. Thatri.

387
00:33:05,960 --> 00:33:07,440
What will you eat?

388
00:33:07,520 --> 00:33:09,400
We have no idea

389
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:11,280
when the next shipment will arrive.

390
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:12,480
It's fine.

391
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:15,280
I am the head of Som Song Saeng house.

392
00:33:15,360 --> 00:33:16,680
If my people are suffering,

393
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,600
I can't just stand by and watch.

394
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:27,600
I know times are hard.

395
00:33:28,760 --> 00:33:30,600
With food and supplies running low,

396
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:33,880
this makes everything feel impossible.

397
00:33:34,920 --> 00:33:37,040
But the only way we'll survive this

398
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:39,560
isn't by being the strongest,

399
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:43,680
it's through our unity.

400
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:45,560
If we are selfish,

401
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:47,800
we will all perish together.

402
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:53,120
But if we are generous
and kind to one another,

403
00:33:55,040 --> 00:33:56,440
we will survive this as one.

404
00:34:02,080 --> 00:34:03,240
Uncle Ree,

405
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:09,600
why don't we combine all our supplies
and cook as one?

406
00:34:09,679 --> 00:34:13,080
It'll be more economical,
and we won't have to cook separate meals.

407
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:17,920
As for the food,
I'll leave all the decisions to you.

408
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:19,920
Miss Rajit.

409
00:34:21,199 --> 00:34:24,280
Do you intend to share
the same meal as the servants?

410
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:27,239
In times like these,
we shouldn't be divided.

411
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:31,639
Whether master or servant,
we're all in the same boat.

412
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:36,000
- Auntie Jiam.
- Yes, miss?

413
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:40,000
I'll need your help in the kitchen.

414
00:34:40,080 --> 00:34:43,800
If we have any yams or taro,
we should cook them with the rice.

415
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:45,360
It'll help stretch our supply further.

416
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:47,719
Of course, miss.
I'll take care of it right away.

417
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:50,400
I'll go dig up some yams and taro.

418
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:52,560
The forest outskirts are full of them.

419
00:34:53,600 --> 00:34:54,679
Thank you, Nid.

420
00:35:10,080 --> 00:35:12,720
Everyone else gets yams mixed with rice.

421
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:15,960
Meanwhile, the owner has to settle
for plain old yams and taro.

422
00:35:21,280 --> 00:35:24,160
That's what happens
when you like to show off to everyone.

423
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:27,200
You end up grumbling
all by yourself when no one's looking.

424
00:35:29,160 --> 00:35:30,680
You came to mock me, is that it?

425
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:35,680
Here. It's salt, pepper,

426
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:37,520
chili flakes, and some honey.

427
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:39,640
I'm sure this'll be better
than eating them plain.

428
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:41,600
Definitely won't be like last time.

429
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:48,000
It's burning!

430
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:49,360
Serves you right.

431
00:35:50,360 --> 00:35:52,760
Maybe your tongue
should've stayed blistered for a few days.

432
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:00,440
Serves you right.

433
00:36:00,520 --> 00:36:03,400
Maybe your tongue
should've stayed blistered for a few days.

434
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:11,640
It smells so good.

435
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:26,600
This tastes way better than before.

436
00:36:27,880 --> 00:36:29,080
Do you like it, Uncle Ree?

437
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:31,640
If you do, I'll bring more.

438
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:33,640
Since you're going to be stuck eating this

439
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:35,320
for a couple months.

440
00:36:37,640 --> 00:36:40,760
Everyone will probably
start calling me Yam-Face.

441
00:36:41,840 --> 00:36:43,720
It's not that bad.

442
00:36:47,200 --> 00:36:48,600
So good.

443
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:50,240
A bit more honey would be good.

444
00:37:03,360 --> 00:37:04,200
Want some?

445
00:37:06,080 --> 00:37:07,080
Want some?

446
00:37:16,720 --> 00:37:20,680
You still haven't told me
where you went when you were gone.

447
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:23,640
I already told you when you were drunk.

448
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:26,000
Well…

449
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:27,960
I don't remember any of it.

450
00:37:28,040 --> 00:37:29,760
Tell me again? Please?

451
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:31,400
Please, Uncle Ree?

452
00:37:31,480 --> 00:37:33,600
Pretty please?

453
00:37:33,680 --> 00:37:35,080
Why would you want to know?

454
00:37:35,760 --> 00:37:38,440
You're so nosy and persistent.

455
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,320
Forget it then.

456
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:46,400
I was in Bangkok.

457
00:37:46,480 --> 00:37:48,680
I had some business to take care of.

458
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:52,720
It's not done yet, but I have a friend
looking after things for me there.

459
00:37:56,280 --> 00:37:57,440
That wasn't so hard.

460
00:37:57,520 --> 00:37:58,600
Such a child.

461
00:37:59,360 --> 00:38:00,880
You're happy when you get your way.

462
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:05,240
Hey,

463
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:09,520
since I've been back,
I haven't seen that ex of yours around.

464
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:13,520
Looking for work, maybe?

465
00:38:13,600 --> 00:38:16,160
Or maybe he finally left.

466
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:18,200
Not that I care enough to check.

467
00:38:20,200 --> 00:38:21,440
You've learned your lesson.

468
00:38:22,200 --> 00:38:24,480
I've decided not to be a fool twice.

469
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:26,600
Looking back,

470
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:30,280
I'm so relieved I got through it.

471
00:38:31,120 --> 00:38:33,640
But the one suffering the consequences now

472
00:38:33,720 --> 00:38:35,120
is Suda.

473
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:38,160
I wonder how she's doing.

474
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:43,920
Spoken like someone who's moved on.

475
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,040
That's good.

476
00:38:47,760 --> 00:38:49,360
Why is that good?

477
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:53,520
Huh?

478
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:55,680
Keeping secrets again?

479
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:01,920
- What is it?
- A spider!

480
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:04,680
Okay. Okay.

481
00:39:04,760 --> 00:39:05,800
- Shoo it away!
- Keep your--

482
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:08,040
- Alright.
- It's coming this way!

483
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:10,920
Go away. Shoo.

484
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:22,400
Long time no see. I thought you'd finally
headed back to Bangkok.

485
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:23,720
If you're here every day,

486
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:27,040
why on earth should I leave?

487
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:35,600
- Rajit.
- Miss Rajit.

488
00:39:38,360 --> 00:39:39,920
I'm sorry, Kajorn,

489
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:41,680
but I have work to attend to today.

490
00:39:43,960 --> 00:39:45,920
Vijarn, let's head to the office.

491
00:39:46,640 --> 00:39:47,520
Certainly.

492
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:05,480
Mr. Kajorn.

493
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:07,720
Yes?

494
00:40:08,880 --> 00:40:10,600
I'd like a word with you.

495
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:13,800
It's about Miss Suda.

496
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:22,240
And why is that?

497
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:24,760
Why should I stay away
from Rajit because you said so?

498
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:26,880
What right do you have to give me orders?

499
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:29,080
I'm asking you nicely, not ordering you.

500
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:30,760
Suda is your wife.

501
00:40:31,840 --> 00:40:34,360
It's your responsibility
to care for her while she's ill.

502
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:40,040
And the fact that you're the one
who ruined her life in the first place.

503
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:45,320
What are you talking about?

504
00:40:46,040 --> 00:40:48,640
I don't care what rumors you've heard,

505
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:50,840
but Suda and I are finished.

506
00:40:50,920 --> 00:40:52,480
Where she lives

507
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:55,120
or how ruined her life is,
that has nothing to do with me.

508
00:40:55,200 --> 00:40:57,200
I've tried to reason with you.

509
00:40:57,280 --> 00:41:00,480
If you insist on being difficult,
don't blame me for being ruthless.

510
00:41:01,120 --> 00:41:03,760
Why? Are you going to tell Rajit?

511
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:06,200
Go ahead. You have no evidence.

512
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:07,840
It's your word against mine.

513
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:10,240
Even if Rajit kicks me out, I'm not going.

514
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:11,880
I'd actually love to see

515
00:41:13,040 --> 00:41:14,960
what you think you can actually do to me.

516
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:17,320
You're not a man.

517
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:21,440
If there was no inheritance,
you'd be long gone.

518
00:41:22,040 --> 00:41:24,120
You're just here for her money.

519
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:27,120
You pathetic pimp.

520
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:38,560
I don't care about
the situation with Suda,

521
00:41:39,680 --> 00:41:42,280
but if you lay a finger on Rajit,
you're a dead man.

522
00:41:57,520 --> 00:41:59,600
The secret's out.

523
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:01,440
What the hell do I do now?

524
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:11,040
Why is this leech so hard to shake off?

525
00:42:11,960 --> 00:42:13,120
He just won't budge.

526
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:19,520
I have to rely on you now, Sri.

527
00:42:24,960 --> 00:42:27,360
You can't do it? Why?

528
00:42:28,040 --> 00:42:30,760
The information you're asking is too deep.

529
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:32,400
I don't know where to begin digging.

530
00:42:33,520 --> 00:42:35,160
How deep can it possibly be?

531
00:42:35,240 --> 00:42:38,080
All I want to know is why Kajorn resigned,

532
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:40,600
if his gambling addiction is real,
which dens did he go to,

533
00:42:40,680 --> 00:42:42,040
and who else is involved.

534
00:42:42,120 --> 00:42:44,160
It's so simple. Why can't you get it done?

535
00:42:44,240 --> 00:42:46,280
These are private matters, madam.

536
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:48,640
People don't even tell
their closest friends these things.

537
00:42:49,320 --> 00:42:52,240
Besides, Kajorn isn't even here.
Where am I supposed to find the trail?

538
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:55,200
You're useless. Just leave already.

539
00:43:04,280 --> 00:43:05,760
Absolutely useless.

540
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:14,040
Hey! Is anyone alive in here?

541
00:43:14,640 --> 00:43:15,960
- Hey!
- I'm coming.

542
00:43:16,040 --> 00:43:18,240
I bought all this stuff,
and no one bothers to help.

543
00:43:18,320 --> 00:43:19,960
- Get to the car, now.
- Yes, sir.

544
00:43:20,040 --> 00:43:21,280
I'm coming, sir.

545
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:22,600
Hurry up.

546
00:43:25,280 --> 00:43:27,360
The laziness in this house.

547
00:43:27,440 --> 00:43:29,400
It's a good thing I had a profitable day,

548
00:43:29,480 --> 00:43:31,480
or I'd be giving each of you
a piece of my mind.

549
00:43:32,080 --> 00:43:33,520
Yeah, it's in the car.

550
00:43:34,840 --> 00:43:36,520
So lazy.

551
00:43:43,720 --> 00:43:44,800
Yes?

552
00:43:45,960 --> 00:43:47,320
Are you feeling okay?

553
00:43:47,400 --> 00:43:48,960
I'm perfectly fine.

554
00:43:49,880 --> 00:43:51,600
Are you tired, Poj?

555
00:43:54,600 --> 00:43:57,240
Why should I waste my time
investigating this nobody?

556
00:43:57,320 --> 00:43:58,400
I have work to do.

557
00:43:58,480 --> 00:44:01,840
It won't take much of your time.
You have connections everywhere.

558
00:44:01,920 --> 00:44:04,720
How many high-ranking officials
are in your debt?

559
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:06,760
Just a few questions to them,

560
00:44:06,840 --> 00:44:08,400
and I'll have everything I need on Kajorn.

561
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:12,640
Too much trouble. I'd rather not.

562
00:44:14,560 --> 00:44:17,760
Wait, are you sure
you don't have a crush on this guy?

563
00:44:17,840 --> 00:44:19,320
Why are you so obsessed with him?

564
00:44:21,520 --> 00:44:23,360
I have a grudge against him. Happy now?

565
00:44:23,440 --> 00:44:24,520
Huh?

566
00:44:24,600 --> 00:44:27,680
Why the attitude? I was just asking.

567
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,760
If you help me with this,

568
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:37,560
I promise I won't go visit Tri
in Chiang Mai.

569
00:44:37,640 --> 00:44:39,080
Do we have a deal?

570
00:44:39,160 --> 00:44:40,960
Are you serious?

571
00:44:43,640 --> 00:44:45,400
You're my wife.

572
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:49,960
Not going to see Thatri should be a given.

573
00:44:50,040 --> 00:44:54,120
Besides, a trip to Chiang Mai
is too exhausting for someone like you.

574
00:44:54,200 --> 00:44:56,160
I don't see how this benefits me at all.

575
00:44:56,240 --> 00:44:57,800
Ugh, Poj.

576
00:44:57,880 --> 00:44:59,400
What's your price then?

577
00:45:00,840 --> 00:45:03,040
I'm not telling.
I think you can guess, can't you?

578
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:10,600
You're a cold-blooded shark.
Always looking for an advantage.

579
00:45:11,560 --> 00:45:13,520
How else do you think I got this rich?

580
00:45:15,960 --> 00:45:16,840
Poj!

581
00:45:16,920 --> 00:45:17,760
Poj.

582
00:45:17,840 --> 00:45:18,960
Let's go.

583
00:45:19,040 --> 00:45:20,160
Put me down.

584
00:45:20,240 --> 00:45:21,200
- Hmm…
- Poj.

585
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:22,920
Poj.

586
00:45:26,480 --> 00:45:27,760
Now,

587
00:45:27,840 --> 00:45:30,520
it's the worst since the war began.

588
00:45:30,600 --> 00:45:33,480
Food is scarce, jobs are non-existent,

589
00:45:33,560 --> 00:45:36,560
and all of Adisuan's products
are sitting idle.

590
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:39,240
Our warehouses are overflowing
with unsold stock.

591
00:45:40,960 --> 00:45:42,920
The market still needs what we have.

592
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:46,160
Agarwood, pearls, and minerals
are always in demand.

593
00:45:46,240 --> 00:45:48,960
It's just the poor economy
and broken logistics.

594
00:45:49,040 --> 00:45:50,680
I believe,

595
00:45:50,760 --> 00:45:54,360
once the war ends, we'll bounce back.

596
00:45:55,240 --> 00:45:56,640
We have enough to last.

597
00:45:58,120 --> 00:46:00,200
What worries me more are the smugglers.

598
00:46:00,280 --> 00:46:01,640
How so, sir?

599
00:46:01,720 --> 00:46:04,560
Colonel Nakamura informed me
that contraband,

600
00:46:04,640 --> 00:46:07,120
mostly food and medicine,

601
00:46:07,200 --> 00:46:09,480
is flooding the market
at ten times the normal rate.

602
00:46:09,560 --> 00:46:11,000
If we let this continue,

603
00:46:11,080 --> 00:46:13,120
it will only crush the people further.

604
00:46:13,960 --> 00:46:15,880
Phuket will be impossible to recover.

605
00:46:20,840 --> 00:46:21,760
Come in.

606
00:46:31,040 --> 00:46:32,520
Sak, what brings you here?

607
00:46:33,760 --> 00:46:37,800
I've come to ask for a huge favor.

608
00:46:47,440 --> 00:46:49,040
I'm not an idiot.

609
00:46:49,120 --> 00:46:51,040
I don't eat grass for breakfast.

610
00:46:52,240 --> 00:46:54,480
Please calm down, Aunt Paetai.

611
00:46:54,560 --> 00:46:56,960
Sak must be in a desperate situation.

612
00:46:57,040 --> 00:46:59,920
Otherwise, he wouldn't have come to us.

613
00:47:01,640 --> 00:47:03,840
But buying up all that tin

614
00:47:03,920 --> 00:47:07,280
at 30 baht per hap is just too much.

615
00:47:07,360 --> 00:47:09,640
It totals over a hundred thousand baht.

616
00:47:09,720 --> 00:47:11,600
That's no small change.

617
00:47:11,680 --> 00:47:14,160
But from what I understand, 30 baht

618
00:47:14,240 --> 00:47:15,440
is the absolute floor price.

619
00:47:15,520 --> 00:47:17,400
He's not asking for anything unreasonable.

620
00:47:18,960 --> 00:47:20,160
Mr. Thatri,

621
00:47:21,080 --> 00:47:23,240
no one wants tin right now.

622
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:24,880
International trade is frozen.

623
00:47:24,960 --> 00:47:27,120
Even if it were free,
nobody would take it.

624
00:47:27,200 --> 00:47:28,480
And once the war is over?

625
00:47:28,560 --> 00:47:30,720
It still won't exceed 30 baht.

626
00:47:30,800 --> 00:47:33,440
Even before the war,
the price was dropping.

627
00:47:33,520 --> 00:47:35,520
Tin isn't like other commodities.

628
00:47:35,600 --> 00:47:37,840
It's unlikely the price will ever recover.

629
00:47:41,320 --> 00:47:43,960
Please, just this once.

630
00:47:44,040 --> 00:47:47,000
I haven't been able to sell
a single gram of tin.

631
00:47:47,080 --> 00:47:49,960
I owe my workers months of back pay,

632
00:47:50,040 --> 00:47:52,320
and after that bombing the other day,

633
00:47:52,400 --> 00:47:54,200
I'm at my wit's end.

634
00:47:55,120 --> 00:47:59,040
If you buy this stock,

635
00:47:59,120 --> 00:48:01,120
my men can survive.

636
00:48:01,200 --> 00:48:03,040
They'll have enough to start over.

637
00:48:05,920 --> 00:48:07,680
Please, have mercy on me.

638
00:48:08,840 --> 00:48:11,120
This isn't a charity ward.

639
00:48:11,200 --> 00:48:14,560
Now get out. Go back the way you came.

640
00:48:16,960 --> 00:48:17,920
Sak,

641
00:48:18,840 --> 00:48:20,920
you haven't even cleared
your debts with us.

642
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:23,960
Coming here to ask for more help
is simply out of the question.

643
00:48:25,000 --> 00:48:25,880
But--

644
00:48:25,960 --> 00:48:27,520
There's mo more buts.

645
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:29,000
This is Adisuan Company money.

646
00:48:29,080 --> 00:48:33,200
Even if you are the heir, you can't just
throw it around as you please.

647
00:48:37,760 --> 00:48:39,560
I'm so sorry.

648
00:48:39,640 --> 00:48:41,720
But we truly cannot accept this.

649
00:48:42,320 --> 00:48:44,000
As Vijarn said,

650
00:48:44,080 --> 00:48:46,360
the price of tin is only going down.

651
00:48:46,440 --> 00:48:48,640
It would be a guaranteed loss for us.

652
00:48:49,280 --> 00:48:51,520
We simply cannot help you.

653
00:48:51,600 --> 00:48:52,440
‪Yes.

654
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:15,560
Father…

655
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:19,240
Mother… I'm sorry.

656
00:49:19,320 --> 00:49:21,400
Sorry I couldn't take care
of the inheritance

657
00:49:21,920 --> 00:49:23,880
as I promised.

658
00:49:36,760 --> 00:49:38,280
I don't have much left to give,

659
00:49:38,880 --> 00:49:41,880
but I hope this is enough
for each of you to start over.

660
00:49:45,960 --> 00:49:48,000
If you buy this stock,

661
00:49:48,080 --> 00:49:50,080
my men can survive.

662
00:49:50,160 --> 00:49:52,040
They'll have enough to start over.

663
00:50:12,520 --> 00:50:14,840
I had a feeling
you wouldn't be able to sleep.

664
00:50:16,560 --> 00:50:18,560
Are you worried about Sak?

665
00:50:20,120 --> 00:50:21,560
Aren't you a clever one?

666
00:50:22,160 --> 00:50:24,160
I'm not a dog.

667
00:50:24,240 --> 00:50:27,680
I just guessed that you have a soft heart.

668
00:50:27,760 --> 00:50:29,960
After seeing Sak in that state,

669
00:50:30,040 --> 00:50:32,080
I knew you wouldn't
be able to just stand by.

670
00:50:32,160 --> 00:50:33,400
Acting smart and all.

671
00:50:34,120 --> 00:50:36,280
And what about you? Why are you still up?

672
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:42,160
I have the same thoughts as you do.

673
00:50:43,400 --> 00:50:45,200
So, you're a softie too.

674
00:50:47,520 --> 00:50:49,880
I was incredibly poor as a child.

675
00:50:50,680 --> 00:50:53,200
If Grandfather hadn't stepped in,

676
00:50:53,280 --> 00:50:55,720
I'd never have made it to Penang.

677
00:50:55,800 --> 00:50:58,080
I might not have even
finished the fourth grade.

678
00:50:59,760 --> 00:51:01,840
Seeing Sak like that,

679
00:51:01,920 --> 00:51:05,000
I can't help but see
my younger self in him.

680
00:51:06,440 --> 00:51:08,360
But everyone else is right.

681
00:51:09,040 --> 00:51:11,160
Helping him means losing money.

682
00:51:11,240 --> 00:51:13,320
As much as I disagree,

683
00:51:13,400 --> 00:51:15,560
I didn't dare speak up

684
00:51:15,640 --> 00:51:17,800
because they were right.

685
00:51:20,720 --> 00:51:23,040
Helping others might hurt us.

686
00:51:23,560 --> 00:51:27,000
Even if it feels wrong,
we have to accept the reality.

687
00:51:32,040 --> 00:51:35,040
So there's really nothing we can do?

688
00:51:52,680 --> 00:51:54,480
Thank you so much.

689
00:51:55,080 --> 00:51:57,640
Are you buying
the entire stock, Mr. Thatri?

690
00:51:57,720 --> 00:52:02,040
Yes, 30 baht per hap,
exactly as you requested.

691
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:06,680
Thatri, dear. I don't think we should be
throwing money down the drain like this.

692
00:52:06,760 --> 00:52:08,240
Don't worry, Fuang.

693
00:52:08,320 --> 00:52:11,360
This is from the private inheritance
left to Rajit and me in the will.

694
00:52:11,440 --> 00:52:13,080
It's not the company's fund.

695
00:52:16,040 --> 00:52:17,880
I'm within my rights to do this, aren't I?

696
00:52:17,960 --> 00:52:19,320
Yes, sir.

697
00:52:20,560 --> 00:52:22,360
Uncle Ree and I have agreed

698
00:52:22,440 --> 00:52:25,880
to split the cost fifty-fifty for the tin.

699
00:52:25,960 --> 00:52:28,800
Please deliver the tin to the warehouse.

700
00:52:28,880 --> 00:52:31,800
- Yes, miss.
- Then, I'll have Vijarn settle the bill.

701
00:52:31,880 --> 00:52:36,120
Yes. I'll get on it right away.

702
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:38,560
Thank you both so much.

703
00:52:43,440 --> 00:52:44,680
Idiots.

704
00:52:44,760 --> 00:52:46,200
You didn't work for that money,

705
00:52:46,280 --> 00:52:48,440
so, of course, you're throwing it away.

706
00:52:50,120 --> 00:52:53,160
Go ahead, bankrupt yourselves.
Live like dogs for all I care.

707
00:53:11,320 --> 00:53:12,240
You're still smiling?

708
00:53:12,880 --> 00:53:15,720
We earned that insult.

709
00:53:15,800 --> 00:53:17,760
It's a loss. I don't know why
I went through with it.

710
00:53:18,280 --> 00:53:20,280
But it's done now.

711
00:53:21,160 --> 00:53:23,800
Besides, we saved so many lives today.

712
00:53:23,880 --> 00:53:27,080
We've already profited so much from them.

713
00:53:27,160 --> 00:53:29,480
We can afford a setback for a change.

714
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:31,880
But it wasn't my money.

715
00:53:33,120 --> 00:53:34,280
I'm sorry, what was that?

716
00:53:39,840 --> 00:53:41,160
I said I'm hungry.

717
00:53:42,320 --> 00:53:44,360
Let's go find something to eat. Come on.

718
00:54:02,160 --> 00:54:05,080
Auntie, I can just have the boiled yams.

719
00:54:05,160 --> 00:54:07,240
Please save this food for the others.

720
00:54:07,320 --> 00:54:10,080
I've already set this aside
for you and Miss Rajit.

721
00:54:10,720 --> 00:54:12,520
It won't take away from others' portion.

722
00:54:12,600 --> 00:54:15,680
I've watched you eat boiled yams
and taro for a week now.

723
00:54:15,760 --> 00:54:17,600
You need a real proper meal.

724
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:20,640
Thank you.

725
00:54:39,120 --> 00:54:40,120
A fish soup?

726
00:54:41,280 --> 00:54:42,600
This is so refreshing.

727
00:54:44,080 --> 00:54:45,000
Is it?

728
00:54:45,080 --> 00:54:46,640
Mmm. Try some.

729
00:54:56,680 --> 00:54:59,000
The Kam Cheng jar…

730
00:55:15,560 --> 00:55:17,600
ADISUAN LUMBER

731
00:55:17,680 --> 00:55:19,720
Our goods aren't selling,

732
00:55:19,800 --> 00:55:21,880
food is being strictly rationed,

733
00:55:21,960 --> 00:55:25,440
and on top of that,
I'm forced to work with those idiots.

734
00:55:26,480 --> 00:55:28,120
I could just kill them both.

735
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:30,600
Pae, don't say things like that.

736
00:55:30,680 --> 00:55:32,560
Someone might hear you.

737
00:55:32,640 --> 00:55:35,720
Besides, those two are our relatives.

738
00:55:36,560 --> 00:55:39,960
They're Uncle Som's relatives, not ours.

739
00:55:40,040 --> 00:55:41,720
And even if they were,

740
00:55:41,800 --> 00:55:44,880
I'd disown anyone
who squanders a fortune like that.

741
00:55:45,520 --> 00:55:48,360
That fortune belongs to them.

742
00:55:48,440 --> 00:55:50,760
As long as they don't touch
the company's funds,

743
00:55:50,840 --> 00:55:53,000
we just have to accept it.

744
00:55:53,080 --> 00:55:55,520
Whatever, you little saint.

745
00:55:56,800 --> 00:55:57,720
One day,

746
00:55:57,800 --> 00:56:00,920
they'll squander everything
and come crawling to us for more.

747
00:56:01,000 --> 00:56:02,640
Using money so foolishly.

748
00:56:03,520 --> 00:56:04,360
Saying it

749
00:56:04,440 --> 00:56:06,600
makes me so resentful of Uncle Som.

750
00:56:06,680 --> 00:56:08,200
He didn't leave us a dime,

751
00:56:08,280 --> 00:56:11,320
yet I still have to work
with those people.

752
00:56:11,920 --> 00:56:14,040
Stop complaining, Pae.

753
00:56:14,120 --> 00:56:17,000
If you appreciate what we have,

754
00:56:17,080 --> 00:56:18,840
It'll save you from all this misery.

755
00:56:22,600 --> 00:56:24,560
In that case, I'll head back now.

756
00:56:25,160 --> 00:56:26,080
Fine.

757
00:56:32,080 --> 00:56:34,240
Her saintly act is annoying.

758
00:56:34,320 --> 00:56:36,880
I can't believe that saint
is actually my sister.

759
00:56:45,760 --> 00:56:46,680
Help me.

760
00:56:47,880 --> 00:56:50,880
Caught him stealing.
I had to teach him a little lesson.

761
00:56:58,840 --> 00:57:00,760
Bury him, and make sure he's gone.

762
00:57:16,520 --> 00:57:19,720
Going this long without a raid,
my hands are going to start itching.

763
00:57:19,800 --> 00:57:21,680
Eliminate Thatri.

764
00:57:21,760 --> 00:57:23,280
If we let him live,

765
00:57:23,360 --> 00:57:25,320
he'll end up being the death of me.

766
00:57:25,400 --> 00:57:27,080
You think you're so good, Thatri?

767
00:57:29,440 --> 00:57:30,760
Mr. Thatri and Miss Rajit

768
00:57:30,840 --> 00:57:32,640
have been kidnapped by Zhang Gong Cheng.

769
00:57:32,720 --> 00:57:33,720
Huh?

770
00:57:33,800 --> 00:57:36,800
Oh my God. I'm so worried.

771
00:57:36,880 --> 00:57:38,760
What if something happened to them?

772
00:57:38,840 --> 00:57:41,920
Please let those two vanish forever.

773
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:43,280
May they never find their way back.

774
00:57:45,280 --> 00:57:46,880
Let's go, Rajit.

775
00:58:18,120 --> 00:58:22,120
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
